## 6. Quick Reference

### charData cheatsheet

```lua
-- Read (always pass true to get {} instead of nil)
local store = charData:get("keyname", true)

-- Write (always pass true to persist across sessions)
charData:set("keyname", store, true)

-- Delete a key inside a stored table
store["mykey"] = nil
charData:set("keyname", store, true)

-- Wipe the whole store
charData:set("keyname", {}, true)
```

### Color codes quick list

```
<red>       errors, warnings
<green>     success, confirmations
<yellow>    notices, unknowns
<white>     headers, labels
<cyan>      data values
```

### table.sort for consistent list output

```lua
local keys = {}
for k in pairs(store) do keys[#keys+1] = k end
table.sort(keys)
for _, k in ipairs(keys) do
  -- display store[k]
end
```

### string.format column alignment

```lua
-- Left-align name in 20 chars, right-align number in 5 chars
string.format("%-20s %5d", name, number)
```

